# RxJS and change detection

## Rule
- Components use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`.
- Templates subscribe via the `async` pipe — never manual `.subscribe()` in components (except for side-effectful one-shots where the result is not rendered).
- Nested subscriptions are forbidden; use `switchMap` / `mergeMap` / `concatMap` / `exhaustMap` with intent.
- Multi-consumer observables apply `shareReplay({ bufferSize: 1, refCount: true })` to avoid duplicate HTTP.

## Why
freightify-web's standards explicitly call out OnPush + async pipe + no nested subscriptions. Default change detection cascades across module federation with noticeable latency; nested subscriptions leak; un-shared streams re-request the backend on every template binding.

## Constraints
- Every new component declares `changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`.
- Manual subscriptions (where unavoidable) unsubscribe via `takeUntilDestroyed()` or `takeUntil(destroy$)`.
- `shareReplay` is applied where the observable feeds more than one template binding or child component.
- Effects/services expose observables; components consume them via the async pipe.

## Examples

### Good
```ts
@Component({ ..., changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush })
class RateCardComponent {
  rate$ = this.facade.rate$.pipe(shareReplay({ bufferSize: 1, refCount: true }));
}
```

### Bad
```ts
ngOnInit() {
  this.ratesApi.list().subscribe(a => a.forEach(x => this.detailsApi.get(x.id).subscribe(d => this.items.push(d))));
}
```

